  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Peel and dice the sweet potatoes and cook them in boiling water until tender.",
    "Meanwhile, cook the paleo-friendly sausage in a pan over medium-high heat, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks.",
    "Add the onion and garlic to the pan and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "Stir in the canned salsa, brine-dried mushrooms, salt, and black pepper.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the cooked sweet potatoes, sausage mixture, and chopped fresh parsley.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish and top with paleo-friendly breadcrumbs and grass-fed butter.",
    "Drizzle the almond milk over the top of the casserole and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the top is golden brown.",
    "Let the casserole rest for 10 minutes before serving."
  ],
